{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/001-welcome/","result":{"data":{"logo":null,"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>So, down with the old one‚Ä¶</h2>\n<p>I‚Äôve opened up the old site to update some docs (and dependencies meanwhile‚Ä¶) and I‚Äôve realized that I didn‚Äôt touch the site since the last two years. Holy shit üò≠\r\nThere was even <code class=\"language-text\">tslint</code> instead of <code class=\"language-text\">eslint</code> in the project‚Ä¶ So I‚Äôve deicided if I have to touch it, I‚Äôll try to make a more professional approach.</p>\n<h2>Times has changed and so the requirements</h2>\n<p>The new site should be:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Easy to maintain. Maybe some .md files in some PR-s, that‚Äôs all. Simple and stupid, with no hassle</li>\n<li>SEO friendly üëâ static. Had some issues in the past with <a href=\"https://info340.github.io/client-side-routing.html\">React Router and Github Pages</a>‚Ä¶</li>\n<li>Should be integrated into CI/CD (that‚Äôs still a ToDo üòä)</li>\n<li>Easy-to-setup locally</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The new candidates</h2>\n<p>So I‚Äôve <del>killed</del> archived the old one and I have to make a replacement. The old site was a react-based SPA. I could do the same with React or Shades but I still had to struggle with routes and SEO‚Ä¶</p>\n<p>First, I‚Äôve checked <a href=\"https://jekyllrb.com/\">Jekyll</a> - as the default approach for Github Pages it‚Äôs easy to setup and deploy. We‚Äôve used it in one of my previous workplace, it does the job pretty well.\r\nThe downside is that I‚Äôm not so familiar with Ruby, <em>gemfiles</em> and other esotheric things, so the stack is totally out of scope. So the templating syntax, theming and stuffs like these.</p>\n<p>The next candidate is <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/\">GatsbyJS</a> - I‚Äôve found a great theme with Typescript support. I‚Äôve updated all deprecated dependencies and it‚Äôs still working. I‚Äôm familiar with the syntax. So far, so good. There are we now.</p>\n<h2>What to expect</h2>\n<p>The plan is to publish announcements like new releases and features, some posts about concepts in FuryStack some techical stuff, development practices and dirty little tricks. But no promises how often will this happen üòâ</p>\n<h2>Coming out next</h2>\n<p>The next step will be setting up the CI/CD and migrating the docs from the old site (or maybe the main monorepo).</p>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, down with the old one‚Ä¶"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I‚Äôve opened up the old site to update some docs (and dependencies meanwhile‚Ä¶) and I‚Äôve realized that I didn‚Äôt touch the site since the last two years. Holy shit üò≠\r\nThere was even "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"tslint"}]},{"type":"text","value":" instead of "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"eslint"}]},{"type":"text","value":" in the project‚Ä¶ So I‚Äôve deicided if I have to touch it, I‚Äôll try to make a more professional approach."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Times has changed and so the requirements"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The new site should be:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Easy to maintain. Maybe some .md files in some PR-s, that‚Äôs all. Simple and stupid, with no hassle"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"c